en held or in single step mode]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>SingleStepMode</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ StepMode prevents moving NextStep into Step until ContinueStepping is commanded]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>160</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>ReadyToStepForward</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ While in StepMode, step has completed and is waiting for StepForward command to proceed to next step]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>168</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Sequencer">ST_StepConfiguration</Name><BitSize>448</BitSize><SubItem><Name>Name</Name><Type>STRING(40)</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Description of the action performed on this step]]></Comment><BitSize>328</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs><Default><String>StepName</String></Default></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Timeout</Name><Type>TIME</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Configurable step timeout. If left set to zero, will be ignored]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>352</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>NextStepAfterRetry</Name><Type>UDINT</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ If left zero, will be ignored and retry returns to current step active. Otherwise can specify a different step to jump to on a fault retry]]></Comment><BitSize>32</BitSize><BitOffs>384</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>IgnoreHold</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ If set to TRUE, this step will ignore the Hold signal and proceed to next step. Useful for critical processes that take more than 1 step to complete]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>416</BitOffs></SubItem></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Sequencer">E_StepState</Name><BitSize>16</BitSize><BaseType>INT</BaseType><EnumInfo><Text>Inactive</Text><Enum>0</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Sequencer is not enabled]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ActiveEntry</Text><Enum>1</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ In this state for 1 scan when entering a step]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ActiveDuring</Text><Enum>2</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ In this state after ActiveEntry. Will stay here until a branch is selected or a fault occurs]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ActiveExit</Text><Enum>3</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Upon a branch being selected during ActiveDuring, will move to this state for 1 scan before changing steps]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>FaultedEntry</Text><Enum>4</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ In this state for 1 scan after a fault occurs during ActiveDuring]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>FaultedDuring</Text><Enum>5</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ In this state after FaultedEntry. Will stay here until a retry or a branch that was configured to CheckWhileFaulted is selected]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>FaultedExit</Text><Enum>6</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ Upon a retry or branch being selected during FaultedDuring, will move to this state for 1 scan before changing step or retrying current step]]></Comment></EnumInfo><EnumInfo><Text>ChangingStep</Text><Enum>7</Enum><Comment><![CDATA[ After ActiveExit and FaultedExit, will move through this state in less than a scan in order to reinitialize step info. Will stay in this step while Held or ReadyToStepForward in SingleStepMode ]]></Comment></EnumInfo><Properties><Property><Name>qualified_only</Name></Property><Property><Name>strict</Name></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="Sequencer">ST_StepStatus</Name><BitSize>2112</BitSize><SubItem><Name>StepState</Name><Type Namespace="Sequencer">E_StepState</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ Step state to drive case statement of actions on]]></Comment><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>0</BitOffs><Default><Value>7</Value></Default></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Active</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ StepState is ActiveEntry, ActiveDuring, or ActiveExit]]></Comment><BitSize>8</BitSize><BitOffs>16</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>Faulted</Name><Type>BOOL</Type><Comment><![CDATA[ StepState is FaultedEntry, FaultedDuring,