|                  |                       |                      |                        |                                          |
+------------------+-----------------------+----------------------+------------------------+------------------------------------------+
|                  |                       |                      |                        |                                          |
+------------------+-----------------------+----------------------+------------------------+------------------------------------------+
|                  |                       |                      |                        |                                          |
+------------------+-----------------------+----------------------+------------------------+------------------------------------------+


===============
1. Introduction
===============
    | This FB is an extremely lightweight and simple way for a programmer to sum the evaluation of many conditions while retaining visibility to the individual conditions in the summation.
      Each condition is set with its own description so that when the overall evaluation is met, a message or error can be raised to indicate which of the many conditions are not met.
      This provides more detail and visibility for ease of troubleshooting.
	  For convenience, the block automatically generate a string called P_Message which contains comma-separated descriptions for which conditions were not met.
	  This P_Message can be added into the error description.
      
    | For example, instead of just passing one BOOL to a Servo to indicate whether or not its Safety is OK, a PermIntlk can be used so that information about every safety device that inhibits the Servo is shared.
      In this way, the Servo can raise the error 'Safety Not OK. Missing: E-Stop 1' or 'Safety Not OK. Missing: Operator Light Curtain, Operator Area Scanner' instead of the more generic 'Safety Not OK'.
	  In the example above, everything after 'Missing: ' is simply the P_Message of the PermIntlk instance.


==========
2. Methods
==========
*Table 1: Summary of Methods*

+-------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
| Method                  | Description                                                                   | Parameter       | Data Type    | Value       | Meaning                                               |
+=========================+===============================================================================+=================+==============+=============+=======================================================+
| M_Set                   | Sets the condition and description configuration for one specified index.     | Index           | USINT        | 0 - 15      | Which index in the array of conditions to set         |
|                         | The array of conditions is by default 0 to 15 however the upper limit can     +-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|                         | be adjusted by modifying the parameter ARRAY_SIZE in Param_PermIntlk.         | Description     | STRING(40)   |             | Description of what the condition means               |
|                         | Similarly, the description is by default 40 chars but this can be adjusted    +-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|                         | by modifying the parameter DESCRIPTION_LEN in Param_PermIntlk.                | Condition       | BOOL         | TRUE/FALSE  | Evaluation of the condition that needs to be met      |
+-------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+


