3. Properties
=============
*Table 2: Summary of Properties*

+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+-------------+-----------------------------------------+
| Property   | Description                                                                                               | Data Type       | Value       | Meaning                                 |
+============+===========================================================================================================+=================+=============+=========================================+
| P_Name     | Functional description of what this permintlk is for. Describes the whole summation, not one condition    | STRING(40)      |             |                                         |
|            | By default this string is 40 chars but this can be adjusted by modifying the parameter DESCRIPTION_LEN    |                 |             |                                         |
|            | in Param_PermIntlk.                                                                                       |                 |             |                                         |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+-------------+-----------------------------------------+
| P_Message  | String of comma-separated descriptions for all conditions that evaluated to FALSE                         | STRING(127)     |             |                                         |
|            | By default this string is 127 chars but this can be adjusted by modifying the parameter MESSAGE_LEN       |                 |             |                                         |
|            | in Param_PermIntlk.                                                                                       |                 |             |                                         |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+-------------+-----------------------------------------+
| P_OK       | Result for all conditions evaluating to true                                                              | BOOL            | TRUE        | All conditions are TRUE                 |
|            |                                                                                                           |                 +-------------+-----------------------------------------+
|            |                                                                                                           |                 | FALSE       | At least one condition is FALSE         |
+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+-------------+-----------------------------------------+


=======================
3. Configuration Sample
=======================
*Declaration Sample:*

.. code:: structured text
    
    PROGRAM MAIN
	VAR
		StartPermissive	: FB_PermIntlk;		//Conditions that must be met in order to start some device
		RunInterlock	: FB_PermIntlk;		//Conditions that must be met for the duration some device is running
		ZoneSafety		: FB_PermIntlk;		//All safety devices that must be ok for zone safety to be ok
	END_VAR
     
          
*Implementation Sample:*
    
.. code:: structured text
    
    //Sample Code Block:
		 
	//Zone Safeties
	ZoneSafety.P_Name:= 'Zone Safety';
	ZoneSafety.M_Set(0, 'Front E-Stop', EStop01.P_DeviceOK);									//Using a safety device as a condition
	ZoneSafety.M_Set(1, EStop02.P_Configuration.Definition.DisplayName, EStop02.P_DeviceOK);	//Using the configured name of the device as the description
	ZoneSafety.M_Set(2, 'Gate Locked', Gate01.P_GateStatus.GateLocked);
	ZoneSafety.M_Set(3, 'Light Curtain', LightCurtain.P_DeviceOK);
	ZoneSafety();		//Call the FB to evaluate the conditions
		 
	//Start Permissives		  
	StartPermissive.P_Name := 'Device01 Start Permissives';
	StartPermissive.M_Set(0, 'MyActuator retracted', MyActuator.P_Status.Retracted);	//Using an actuator position as a condition
	StartPermissive.M_Set(1, 'MyServo01 at Move 1: Home', MyServo01.M_CheckAtPosition(Position:= MyServo01Moves[1].Position, Tolerance := 0.5);	//Using a servo position as a condition
	StartPermissive.M_Set(		//Using multiple lines when one line is too long for the screen
		Index := 2,
		Description:= CONCAT(CONCAT('MyServo02 at Move 5: Pounce (', MyServo02Moves[5].Position), 'mm)'),	//Inserting useful info into the description
		Condition := MyServo02.M_CheckAtPosition(Position:= MyServo02Moves[5].Position, Tolerance := 1.0);
	StartPermissive();	//Call the FB to evaluate the conditions
		 
	//Run Interlocks	 
	RunInterlock.P_Name := 'Device01 Run Interlocks';
	RunInterlock.M_Set(0, ZoneSafety.P_Message, ZoneSafety.P_OK);	//Using the evaluation of a different permintlk as a condition "Perm-ception"(TM)
	RunInterlock.M_Set(1, 'MyRobot Clear of Fixture1', MyRobot.P_ZoneHolds.DO73_ClrOfFix1);	//Using a robot clear of fixture as a condition
	RunInterlock();		//Call the FB to evaluate the conditions
 
     
