+------------------+-----------------------+----------------------+------------------------+------------------------------------------+


===============
1. Introduction
===============
    | The Sequencer FB is the one-stop shop for everything you need to control a sequencer. It manages both the overall behavior of the sequencer and also each individual step.
	  At the sequence level, it provides ways to enable/disable a sequence, configure what the first step is, hold a sequence (prevent moving to next step), retry faults, and also use single step mode.
	  At the step level it manages the step state to provide clear cases for where to add logic. It also provides several branches (ways to exit a step) each with their own coonditions that must be met and configurable next step.

==========
2. Methods
==========
*Table 1: Summary of Methods*

+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
| Method                    | Description                                                                   | Parameter       | Data Type    | Value       | Meaning                                               |
+===========================+===============================================================================+=================+==============+=============+=======================================================+
| M_AddFaultCondition       | Adds an error for the current step to monitor while in ActiveDuring           | Error           | REFERENCE TO |             |                                                       |
|                           | If the Error.Active is TRUE, the step will capture this error, stop checking  |                 | ST_Error     |             |                                                       |
|                           | other fault conditions, and move the step state to FaultedEntry               |                 |              |             |                                                       |
+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
| M_AddFaultConditionCustom | Adds a custom error for the current step to monitor while in ActiveDuring for | Active          | BOOL         |             |                                                       |
|                           | cases when there isn't already an ST_Error instance that can be passed        +-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|                           | directly using M_AddFaultCondition                                            | ID              | UDINT        |             |                                                       |
|                           |                                                                               +-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|                           |                                                                               | Description     | STRING(40)   |             |                                                       |
+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+
| M_Retry                   | If this is called when in FaultedDuring, this will check if there is a        |                 |              |             |                                                       |
|                           | configured NextStepAfterRetry and will move to that step's ActiveEntry.       |                 |              |             |                                                       |
|                           | If NextStepAfterRetry = 0, it will move back to current step's ActiveEntry    |                 |              |             |                                                       |
+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------+--------------+-------------+-------------------------------------------------------+


