================
1. Introduction
================
    | Tesla State Machine or TSM is the overall controller or orchestrator for a grouping of equipment.
    | This is the base FB to be extended for creating unique TSMs.  The built in sequencers should be utilized to facilitate the machine state transitions.
    | The state machine diagram can be found in document TS-0014078.  This document illustrates the flow of each state and possible transitions.
    | FB_TSM controls the modes and state of an Equipment, and during these states, it executes commands on child EMs, stringing EM transitions together to perform the high-level process.

*Declaration Sample:*

| Create FB that extends FB_TSM
FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_TemplateStation_TSM EXTENDS FB_TSM
VAR
     // declare instances of child EMs here
END_VAR

| Create instance
VAR
    fbTemplateTSM				: FB_TemplateStation_TSM;
END_VAR

*Implementation Sample:*

// Configuration
	fbTemplateTSM.P_Configuration.Definition.displayName  := 'Template TSM';
	fbTemplateTSM.P_Configuration.Definition.description  := 'Template TSM Description';
	fbTemplateTSM.P_Configuration.Definition.deviceType   := 'TSM';
	fbTemplateTSM.P_Configuration.Definition.categoryName := 'Template Station';
	fbTemplateTSM.P_Configuration.Definition.parentName   := 'Template Station';

// Call TSM
	fbTemplateTSM();

| The following Methods must be created and programmed appropriately

    _M_Aborting
    _M_Homing
    _M_Pausing
    _M_Proceeding
    _M_Running

================
2. Library Index
================
